  "body": "I can't seem to set scrollTop or even simulate a scroll for a component within my unit tests.\n\nFor example:\n\n``` javascript\nconst component = TestUtils.renderIntoDocument(<.../>);\nconst node = React.findDOMNode(component);\nnode.scrollTop = 290;\nTestUtils.Simulate.scroll(node, { target: node });\n```\n\nDebugging through it seems after scrollTop set, its still 0. Scroll handler does get called, but scrollTop still returns 0. scrollHeight also returns 0. Normally thats because it cant scroll, but the elements seem right to me -- height smaller than the contained object's height, etc.\n\nrender function:\n\n``` javascript\nrender(){\n    return (\n        <div style={...} onScroll={this.onScroll}>\n            {this.props.children}\n        </div>\n    );\n}\n```\n\nElements:\n\n``` html\n<div style=\"overflow-y:scroll;height:80px;\" data-reactid=\".0\">\n    <div style=\"height:900px;display:block;width:500px;\" data-reactid=\".0.0\">\n    </div><span data-reactid=\".0.1\"></span>\n</div>\n```\n",
